we can manipulate DOM using console or selecting elements on the webpage .
like selecting classes , id ot particular tags .
Three types of selectors are there :-
1) getElementById()
2) getElementByclassName()
3) querySelector()

suppose there is an element with id=title.
then we can store that element in a variable like
//                       const myFirst=document.getElementById('title')
we can access different id names , classname
                      document.getElementById('title').id         // print id
                      document.getElementById('title').classname  // prints class 
      document.getElementById('title').getAttributes() // gives all the attributes used.
       document.getElementById('title').setAttributes() // used to set new attributes.
    ex- document.getElementById('title').setAttributes('class','heading') //
                   a new class named heading has been added
                  myFirst.style.backgroundColor="green"
                myFirst.style.padding="10px"    // changing some style to the id.

now , innerText, innerHTML, textcontent 
innerHTML: (tags + text)
textcontent: Raw text only, Includes hidden text
innerText: Rendered (visible) text, Matches what the user actually sees


we can use querySelector to select any element , wheather it is id, classname or tag.
querySelector('h1') := selects the first h1 element.
querySelector(#title):= # is used to select the id
querySelector(.heading):= . is used to select class.
querySelectorAll():= it is used to select all elements.

document.getElementsByClassName("item"); // HTMLCollection
document.getElementsByTagName("div");    // HTMLCollection
document.querySelectorAll(".item");      // NodeList

we can convert nodelist/htmlcollection to Array
const array = Array.from(nodes);

at nodelist we cannot directly access each element , we need to give index no to access it .
After converting it to array, we can use foreach and map method.

ex:= document.querySelectorAll('h2')
we get a nodelist of all h2
now to access each h2 , either we use foreach loop or 
const h2All=document.querySelectorAll('h2')
h2All[0].innerText
